When the temperature jumps back to T = 0.9, the distribution function evolves very quickly to a nonchaotic situation. The ﬁnal situation, corresponding to the distribution function displayed with red points, is a perfect example of memory eﬀects in Spin Glasses. The system at this point explores the same conﬁgurations that used to explore before the temperature jump, just as its excursion to T = 0.5 never happened.

